From 35bae29b56340cf0d450db74c99fa83c30eb3650 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Vincze <david.vincze@arm.com>
Date: Thu, 2 Apr 2026 09:36:31 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 01/17] Add generated files to the source tree

Generated files are now automatically created when invoking CMake.
However, not all components of TF-M use CMake to consume TF-PSA-Crypto
but include source files directly instead. Furthermore, subsequent patch
files also rely on the presence of these files in the source tree.

As the TF-PSA-Crypto documentation states, the content of these files
depends only on the TF-PSA-Crypto source, not on the platform or on the
library configuration.

Change-Id: I54a759a1480c4d088525cc00a208694c5fde9daf
Signed-off-by: David Vincze <david.vincze@arm.com>
---
